      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "To The Honorable Socitye [society] From the Humble Pititioner [petitioner] of the Age [aged] Wife of John Slurgent [Sturgeon] Who was Drownd [drowned] in Charles Town and I am forlorn and Not able to help My Self and Beg the Assitance [assistance] of his own Contry [country] Socity [society] and in hopes they Will Guive [give] me Som [some] assittance [assistance] As i am one of that Contry My Self South [furthing?] Crage Porting Crage [South FerryPort on Craig, modern day Tayport] Near St. andrewes in the Contry Now i am A Widow 5 years and Never Trobeled [troubled] anny [any] one of you poor hellpless [helpless] men as Begs you wold [would] Take Notis [notice] of Me and givve [give] me Som [some] Asistant [assistance]  So I Conclude and Begs Yur [your] assistance\n \nAnn Slurgent [Sturgeon]\n\nWill Be in Duty Bound to Pray of you And Yours."
    },
